title: Blac Chyna Slams Tyga for Allegedly Not Paying Child Support: He 'Wanted to See Me Fail'
text: Blac Chyna Slams Tyga for Allegedly Not Paying Child Support: He 'Wanted to See Me Fail' by Elisa Osegueda 9:32   Blac Chyna has got a lot on her mind. The 28-year-old reality star took to Snapchat on Wednesday to get a few things off her chest and, as it turns out, her fury was directed at her ex-boyfriend, Tyga, for allegedly not paying child support and publicly talking about their 4-year-old son, King Cairo. In a series of snaps, Chyna alleges that following her split from Tyga, he kicked her out of his home and "wanted to see me fail!" She also claims that Tyga did not provide her with child support. Photo: Snapchat She then references Tyga's recent interview with People , where the rapper claims King "is very spoiled." "Telling my business about King," Chyna wrote. "I bet any money! I got more money then ur account Tyga, Michael! Photo: Snapchat Photo: Snapchat “So go tell Kylie [Jenner], and Rob [Kardashian]! About our son account!" she continued. "Cause that’s the only reason I’m contacting [you]! But u wanna make it like I want u lol!” "Tyga ur a b**ch! An u can go get ur mom," she concluded before posting an address located in California, which turned out to be the address to her beauty boutique. WATCH: Blac Chyna Says She’s ‘in It for the Long Haul’ With Rob Kardashian: 'We're Fighting for Each Other' In a recent interview with Cosmopolitan , Chyna opened up about her relationship with Tyga, whom she believes came into her life for the sake of having their son. "I really feel people are in your life for seasons or reasons, and the reason I was with Tyga was to have King,” she explained. “Tyga and I dated and we found something in each other, there was love there, and the outcome of that was King."
